    <title>Prerequisite Review</title>

    <p>These exercises cover topics from MTH 20. These are prerequisite skills to succeed in this class. If you have trouble completing any of these exercises, you should make time as soon as possible to review this material with your instructor or with a tutor.</p> 

    <exercise>
        <title>Adding integers and decimals</title>
        <webwork>
            <statement>
                <p><ol label="a">
                    <li>
                        <p><m>37+106+9=</m><var name="152" width="10" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><m>53+7=</m><var name="60" width="10" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><m>4.6+0.87=</m><var name="5.47" width="10" /></p>
                    </li>
                </ol></p>
            </statement>
        </webwork>
    </exercise>
    <exercise>
        <title>Adding mixed numbers</title>
        <webwork>
            <setup>
                <pg-code>
                    Context("LimitedProperFraction");
                    Context()->flags->set(requireProperFractions=>0);
                    $a=Fraction(5+1/5+6+2/3);
                    $b=Fraction(2+2/3+1+1/3);
                    $c=Fraction(6+2/5+3+1/3);
                    $d=Fraction(5+1/2+2+4/5);
                </pg-code>
            </setup>
            <statement>
                <p><ol label="a">
                    <li>
                        <p><m>5\frac{1}{5}+6\frac{2}{3}=</m><var name="$a" width="10" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><m>2\frac{2}{3}+1\frac{1}{3}=</m><var name="$b" width="10" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><m>6\frac{2}{5}+3\frac{1}{3}=</m><var name="$c" width="10" /></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p><m>5\frac{1}{2}+2\frac{4}{5}=</m><var name="$d" width="10" /></p>
                    </li>
                </ol></p>
            </statement>
        </webwork>
    </exercise>
